docs.abstract: The soaring electricity demands of data centers and A.I. are straining the grid in some areas, pushing up emissions and slowing the energy transition.
docs.snippet: The soaring electricity demands of data centers and A.I. are straining the grid in some areas, pushing up emissions and slowing the energy transition.
docs.lead_paragraph: A few weeks ago, I joined a small group of reporters for a wide-ranging conversation with Bill Gates about climate change, its causes and potential solutions. When the topic turned to the issue of just how much energy artificial intelligence was using, Gates was surprisingly sanguine.

headline.print_headline: A.I.’s Insatiable Energy Use Drives Electricity Demands

docs.abstract: The tech giant’s revenue also grew 15 percent, but Wall Street is watching whether its investment in A.I. is paying off for its cloud computing business.
docs.snippet: The tech giant’s revenue also grew 15 percent, but Wall Street is watching whether its investment in A.I. is paying off for its cloud computing business.
docs.lead_paragraph: Microsoft closed its first full fiscal year of aggressive artificial intelligence investment with a mixed bag of results for people worried about how much big tech companies are spending on A.I.

headline.main: Microsoft Profit Jumps 10%, but Cloud Computing Grows Less Than Expected
headline.print_headline: Microsoft Quarterly Profit Rose 10%, but Cloud Computing Business Grows Less Than Expected

docs.abstract: Airlines, hospitals and people’s computers were affected after CrowdStrike, a cybersecurity company, sent out a flawed software update.
docs.snippet: Airlines, hospitals and people’s computers were affected after CrowdStrike, a cybersecurity company, sent out a flawed software update.
docs.lead_paragraph: Airlines grounded flights. Operators of 911 lines could not respond to emergencies. Hospitals canceled surgeries. Retailers closed for the day. And the actions all traced back to a batch of bad computer code.

headline.main: Chaos and Confusion: Tech Outage Causes Disruptions Worldwide
headline.print_headline: Software Update Goes Awry, Causing Chaos Throughout the World

docs.lead_paragraph: Earlier this year, Satya Nadella hammered out a deal that surprised everyone outside his inner circle at Microsoft.

headline.print_headline: A Risk-Taker Leaps Into a New Technology

docs.abstract: As diagnoses of autism rise, Microsoft and other large companies are working to better support autistic workers so they can thrive without “masking.”
docs.snippet: As diagnoses of autism rise, Microsoft and other large companies are working to better support autistic workers so they can thrive without “masking.”
docs.lead_paragraph: When Chelsia Potts took her 10-year-old daughter to a psychologist to be tested for autism spectrum disorder, she decided almost as an afterthought to be tested herself. The result came as a surprise. Like her daughter, Ms. Potts was diagnosed with autism.

headline.main: Employees With Autism Find New Ways to Navigate the Workplace

docs.abstract: While in some corners of Silicon Valley people worry about the risks of A.I., a simple failed software update caused a worldwide outage.
docs.snippet: While in some corners of Silicon Valley people worry about the risks of A.I., a simple failed software update caused a worldwide outage.
docs.lead_paragraph: For a couple of years now, the artificial intelligence community has been warning that there is a chance their work will go south and humanity will end in a conflagration worthy of a superhero movie.

headline.main: When Tech Fails, It Is Usually With a Whimper Instead of a Bang
headline.print_headline: When Tech Fails, It Is Usually With a Whimper, Not a Bang

docs.abstract: New research from the Data Provenance Initiative has found a dramatic drop in content made available to the collections used to build artificial intelligence.
docs.snippet: New research from the Data Provenance Initiative has found a dramatic drop in content made available to the collections used to build artificial intelligence.
docs.lead_paragraph: For years, the people building powerful artificial intelligence systems have used enormous troves of text, images and videos pulled from the internet to train their models.

headline.main: The Data That Powers A.I. Is Disappearing Fast
headline.print_headline: The Data That Powers A.I.  Is Disappearing Fast

docs.abstract: Transportation Secretary Pete Buttigieg singled out the airline on Sunday for ongoing disruptions and “unacceptable” customer service as it continued to cancel flights.
docs.snippet: Transportation Secretary Pete Buttigieg singled out the airline on Sunday for ongoing disruptions and “unacceptable” customer service as it continued to cancel flights.
docs.lead_paragraph: Three days after planes around the world were grounded by a technology outage, Delta Air Lines was struggling to get stranded passengers to their destinations on Monday and was the only carrier still canceling hundreds of flights as it raced to update its  systems.

headline.main: Delta Cancels More Flights as It Struggles to Recover From Tech Outage

docs.abstract: The move adds more than 500 to the unionized video game staff at Microsoft, which has pledged to remain neutral on organizing efforts.
docs.snippet: The move adds more than 500 to the unionized video game staff at Microsoft, which has pledged to remain neutral on organizing efforts.
docs.lead_paragraph: More than 500 workers in the team behind World of Warcraft, one of the most popular video games in the world, have voted to unionize, the Communications Workers of America said on Wednesday.

docs.abstract: As regulatory scrutiny picks up, the tech giant says it is pleased with the progress OpenAI has made with governance and considers its oversight role unnecessary.
docs.snippet: As regulatory scrutiny picks up, the tech giant says it is pleased with the progress OpenAI has made with governance and considers its oversight role unnecessary.
docs.lead_paragraph: Microsoft has given up its seat on OpenAI’s board, relinquishing a nonvoting position it gained late last year, as regulators intensify their scrutiny of the ties between the tech giant and the start-up behind the chatbot ChatGPT.

headline.print_headline: Under Regulator Scrutiny, Microsoft Surrenders OpenAI Board Seat
